<br>
Looking down to scan the ground for food, she becomes entranced by the play of the mist swirling around her feet.  She does a little dance as she goes, trying to make the patterns more and more elaborate.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  &quot;What the-&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Stopping suddenly, she reaches down and picks up a piece of seaweed.  A quizzical expression upon her face, she smells the seaweed.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  &quot;Well, that's what it is, and I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> am</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> hungry.&quot;  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mircha thoughtfully chews on the salty stuff, wondering how it got out here in the forest to begin with.  Screwing up her nose, she reaches in and pulls a long blond hair out of her mouth. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;Euch, how did that get in there?&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  She quickly feels her head, and touches short hair that she hopes is still dark. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;I must be tired, I'm imagining things.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Down at her feet, she notices that the mist is thicker, and the trees have tapered off almost completely.  Hoping that means what she thinks it does, she walks to where the mist is rising highest, and is rewarded by the sight of a large pond with a rock in the center.  Hurrying to the edge of the pond, she carefully places her precious pack down, and lays her cloak over it.  Kneeling down the the water, she pushes the mist aside, and steals a glance at her reflection.  She sighs, relieved, and cups her hands together to drink, and rinse her dusty face.  Green fingers encircle her wrists, and she jerks them back with a gasp, but the fingers have her wrists firmly.  Before she can dig in her heals, or start to sing, she is pulled headlong into the icy morning waters.<br>
<br>
The mists swirl in treacherously, erasing any trace of her presence on the shore of a moment before.  All is still by the shore of the pond.  The only sound is of the earliest birds chirruping in the trees nearby.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
